.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINYEARMONTH.YEAR" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainYearMonth.year \- Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.year
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]year\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] instances returns an integer
representing the number of years of this year\-month relative to the
start of a calendar\-specific epoch year.
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]year\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
Use the \f[CR]with()\f[R] method to create a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object with the desired new value.
.PP
For general information and more examples, see
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.year\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using year
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] ym = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-07\(dq); \f[I]// ISO 8601 calendar\f[R]
console.log(ym.year); \f[I]// 2021\f[R]
.EE
